CSS - CASCADING STYLE SHEETS
defined inside <style> tag or in separate css file
eg:
body {
	background-color: gray;
	font-size:30px;
}
p{
	color:green;
}
css provides absolute and relative units to define a length
it is expressed by a number value + unit
Absolute units do not change between different screen sizes
cm, mm, in, px, pt, pc
Relative units will change between different screens automatically
%, em. rem, vw,vh, vmin, vmax

body, p{
	background-color: gray;
	font-size:30px;
}
body {
	background-color: rgba(0,0,0,0,4);
	margin:calc(2em*5em);
}

CSS ANIMATION
animation and transition property
 
CSS MEDIA QUERIES:
it allow you to define specific rulesets for different screen sizes(responsive css)
min-width: 650px


